'''Mark Jones''' ([[April 22]], [[1930s|1939]] - [[January 14]], [[2010]])<ref name="BFI" /> played [[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Nemet]] in [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']].

He appeared in numerous British productions beginning in 1967; notable roles include the 1974 sex comedy ''Keep It Up, Jack'', a recurring role in a 1976 arc of ''Doctor Who'' (alongside [[Tom Baker]]) and the 1979 action film ''Bear Island'' (with [[Christopher Lee]]). His final credited role was in the 1999 science fiction comedy series ''Red Dwarf'', which also featured fellow ''Star Wars'' alumni [[Hugh Quarshie]] and [[Don Henderson]].

Jones passed away on January 14, 2010.<ref name="BFI" />

